The paper discusses channel estimation and interference mitigation in massive MIMO systems, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a non-iterative scheme for uplink channel estimation and a hybrid system that combines time-multiplexed and superimposed pilots, which are related to system design and control (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of interference on the system performance, which is relevant to communication and networking (cs.COM).
